VERDICT: confirmed-but-no-uca
REASON: Both halves of the oracle reproduce on HEAD. Verus witness: src/mpu.rs:131-144 validate_region(0x8000_0000, 0x8000_0000) returns true because (size & size-1)==0, size>=32, and (base & size-1)==0 all hold on that pair (by pure bit-arithmetic facts the existing is_power_of_two bit_vector proof at lines 98-110 already certifies). But regions_overlap's requires at lines 161-162 demands r.base as int + r.size as int <= u32::MAX as int, and 0x1_0000_0000 > 0xFFFF_FFFF, so an accepted region is unusable by the only overlap checker — the P1 ∧ P3 combination claimed in the module header is refuted by a single pair of witness values. The precondition is never discharged at the call site because validate_region_set is #[verifier::external_body] (line 185), so Verus silently accepts the function body and the proof obligation is dropped. PoC: with r1=(0x8000_0000, 0x8000_0000) and r2=(0x9000_0000, 0x1000) both pass validate_region; in release mode r1.base + r1.size on line 169 wraps to 0, so r2.base < r1_end (0x9000_0000 < 0) is false and regions_overlap returns false for a region strictly contained in the other — the exact scenario the m2_containment_overlap test (tests/mpu_integration.rs:104-116) asserts must be rejected. In debug the same line panics inside the MPU configuration path, which is itself a safety failure. The scenario is within target (ARMv7-M PMSAv7 allows N=30 size=2GB at base=0 or 0x8000_0000 — the m5_max_region_size test comment at tests/mpu_integration.rs:260 even notes 2GB regions are contemplated, while silently assuming "Aligned at 0 — the only valid base", an assumption the code does not enforce). Not a documented caller precondition; not unsupported core count; not a known limitation (stub lemmas lemma_validate_region_spec, lemma_misaligned_rejected, lemma_below_minimum_rejected, lemma_common_regions_valid at lines 227-269 have empty or `ensures true` bodies, so P1 is not actually proven). The Lean model proofs/lean/MpuRegion.lean uses Nat (unbounded), so the model cannot exhibit the bug — classical proof-code drift between the u32 implementation and the ideal-arithmetic spec. No UCA maps: artifacts/stpa.yaml explicitly scopes UCAs out; docs/research/deep-zephyr-analysis.md's UCA-MEM-1..5 cover heap/slab allocators, not MPU region validation. Recommend filing a new UCA-MPU-1 ("validate_region_set returns true for a region configuration whose base+size overflows u32, silently disabling userspace memory isolation"), feeding a new hazard (analogue of H-5 but for isolation rather than stack), leading to L-1 / L-2.
